        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 5 at 5:37PM PDT by NWS Portland OR</headline>
        <description>At 536 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southwest of Marion Forks, or 13 miles south of Detroit, moving
northwest at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Detroit, Mill City, Idanha, Marion Forks, and Gates.

In Oregon this includes State Highway 22 east of Salem between mile
markers 28 and 58, and between mile markers 67 and 77.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
